			<node ID="ID_553532230" TEXT="In general when the method of variation of parameters is applied to the second&#8208;order nonhomogeneous linear differential equation . with y = v 1 ( x) y 1 + v 2 ( x) y 2 (where y h = c 1 y 1 +c 2 y 2 is the general solution of the corresponding homogeneous equation) the two conditions on v 1 and v 2 will always be ." />
