		<node ID="ID_1097741142" LINK="https://towardsdatascience.com/probability-concepts-explained-probability-distributions-introduction-part-3-4a5db81858dc" TEXT="Probability concepts explained: probability distributions ">
			<node ID="ID_809563727" TEXT="A probability distribution is a list of outcomes and their associated probabilities. We can write small distributions with tables but it&#8217;s easier to summarise large distributions with functions. A function that represents a discrete probability distribution is called a probability mass function." />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_958034424" LINK="https://stattrek.com/probability-distributions/probability-distribution.aspx" TEXT="Probability Distribution - Statistics and Probability">
			<node ID="ID_1360733188" TEXT="A probability distribution is a table or an equation that links each outcome of a statistical experiment with its probability of occurrence. Consider the coin flip experiment described above. The table below which associates each outcome with its probability is an example of a probability distribution." />
