			<node ID="ID_1356643277" TEXT="Significance-based hypothesis testing is the most common framework for statistical hypothesis testing. An alternative framework for statistical hypothesis testing is to specify a set of statistical models one for each candidate hypothesis and then use model selection techniques to choose the most appropriate model." />
