			<node ID="ID_587899097" TEXT="Conformal maps in two dimensions. If is an open subset of the complex plane  then a function: &#8594; is conformal if and only if it is holomorphic and its derivative is everywhere non-zero on .If is antiholomorphic (conjugate to a holomorphic function) it preserves angles but reverses their orientation.. In the literature there is another definition of conformal: a mapping which is one-to-one " />
