		<node ID="ID_808564460" LINK="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/ConformalMapping.html" TEXT="Conformal Mapping -- from Wolfram MathWorld">
			<node ID="ID_1759501469" TEXT="A conformal mapping also called a conformal map conformal transformation angle-preserving transformation or biholomorphic map is a transformation w=f(z) that preserves local angles. An analytic function is conformal at any point where it has a nonzero derivative. Conversely any conformal mapping of a complex variable which has continuous partial derivatives is analytic." />
